Figs_1a_3a_microbiome_overview

Eric Leung, Erin Dahl, and Lisa Karstens, PhD

Last Updated: 2022-03-10

  • Purpose
  • Plot stacked bar plots and perform statistical and cluster analyses

Purpose

This Rmd documents the code used for the analysis presented in Figures 1a and 3a of the manuscript Network-based differences in the vaginal and bladder microbial communities between women with and without urgency urinary incontinence by Nardos et al.

## Libraries needed
library(phyloseq)
library(dendextend)
library(visdat)
library(clValid)
library(dplyr)
library(tibble)
library(here)
library(ggplot2)
library(forcats)
library(microshades)
library(cowplot)
library(patchwork)


# load data
load(here("data", "sufu_tree_ps_rel.RData"))

Plot stacked bar plots and perform statistical and cluster analyses

Create clustering and abundance figures for vaginal microbiome

sample_names(ps_vs_rel) <- sample_data(ps_vs_rel)$sequence_id

  # Clustering work -----
  set.seed(1000)
  ps_vs_f <- UniFrac(ps_vs_rel, weighted = TRUE)
## Warning in UniFrac(ps_vs_rel, weighted = TRUE): Randomly assigning root as --
## GCAAGCGTTATCCGGATTTACTGGGTGTAAAGGGAGCGCAGGCGGTTTGGCAAGTTGAGAGTGGAAGCAGGGGGCTCAACCCCCTGACTGCTCCCAAAACTGTTAAACTTGAGTATGGGAGAGGCAGGCGGAATTCCTAGTGTAGCGGTGAAATGCTTAGATATTAGGAAGAACACCGGTGGCGAAGGCGGCCTGCTGGACCAAAACTGACGCTGAGGCTCGAAAGCGTG
## -- in the phylogenetic tree in the data you provided.
  set.seed(2001)
  ps_vs_hc <- hclust(ps_vs_f, method = "ward.D2")

  # Convert hclust into a dendrogram
  ps_vs_hcd <- as.dendrogram(ps_vs_hc)

  # Cluster validation
  clmethods <- c("hierarchical")
  internal_val <- clValid(
    as.matrix(ps_vs_f),
    nClust = 2:6,
    clMethods = clmethods,
    validation = "internal")
  
  summary(internal_val)

  # Setup to color samples
  vhcd_labs_init <-
    ps_vs_hcd %>%
    labels() %>%
    data.frame(sample_id = ., stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
  vhcd_cohort <-
    ps_vs_rel %>%
    sample_data() %>%
    data.frame() %>%
    rownames_to_column("sample_id") %>%
    select(cohort_sufu, sample_name, subject_id, sample_id,
           menopause_status, estrogen_use, vaginal_products_any) %>%

    # Specify for cohort information
    # Cases = orange
    # Controls = blue
    mutate(color = if_else(cohort_sufu == "case", "orange", "blue")) %>%
    mutate(shape = if_else(cohort_sufu == "case", 18, 19)) %>%

    # Specify for menopause status
    # Black is post-menopause, White is premenopause
    mutate(menopause_stat_color =
             if_else(menopause_status == "Post-Menopause", "black", "white")) %>%

    # Specify vaginal product use
    # Black is vaginal product use, White none
    mutate(vp_use_color =
             if_else(vaginal_products_any == TRUE, "black", "white"))

  
  vhcd_labs <- left_join(vhcd_labs_init, vhcd_cohort, by = "sample_id")

  # Stacked bar plot of taxa -----
  vs_psmelt_rel_top <-
    ps_vs_rel %>%
    psmelt() %>%
    select(sequence_id, Abundance, subject_id, sample_origin,
          sample_name, Phylum, Genus)%>%
    mutate(sequence_id = fct_relevel(sequence_id, vhcd_labs$sample_id))

  color_obj <- create_color_dfs(vs_psmelt_rel_top)
  vs_cdf <- color_obj$cdf
  plot_vs <- plot_microshades(color_obj$mdf, vs_cdf, x = "sequence_id") +
    theme(axis.title.x = element_blank(),
          axis.text.x = element_blank(),
          axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
          legend.position = "none")
  
  mdf_name_change <- color_obj$mdf %>% rename (Sample = sequence_id)
  vs_legend <- custom_legend(mdf_name_change, color_obj$cdf)
## Warning: Removed 525 rows containing missing values (geom_col).
## Warning: Removed 378 rows containing missing values (geom_col).
## Warning: Removed 1240 rows containing missing values (geom_col).
## Warning: Removed 612 rows containing missing values (geom_col).
  # Plot dendrogram -----

  par(mar = c(3, 2, 1, 1))
  origin_mar <- par(no.readonly = TRUE)
  ps_vs_dend <-
    ps_vs_hcd %>%
    dendextend::set("leaves_col", vhcd_labs$color) %>%
    dendextend::set("leaves_pch", vhcd_labs$shape) %>%
    dendextend::set("leaves_cex", 1) %>%
    dendextend::set("labels", rep("", nrow(vhcd_labs)))
  ps_vs_dend %>% plot()
  colored_bars(colors =
                 vhcd_labs %>%
                 select(menopause_stat_color,
                        vp_use_color) %>%
                 rename(MENOP = menopause_stat_color,
                        VPROD = vp_use_color),
               dend = ps_vs_dend,
               sort_by_labels_order = FALSE)
  dendextend::rect.dendrogram(ps_vs_dend, k = 2, border = 8, lty = 5, lwd = 2, lower_rect = -.2)

  par(origin_mar)

  plot_vs

  plot_grid(vs_legend)

  # Test cluster significance -----
  cluster_vs_df <-
    vhcd_labs %>%
    left_join(
      bind_cols(
        order = ps_vs_hc$order,
        sample_id = ps_vs_hc$labels,
        cluster = cutree(ps_vs_dend, k = 2)),
      by = "sample_id"
    )

  # Cohort
  cluster_vs_df %>%
    select(cluster, cohort_sufu) %>%
    table() %>%
    fisher.test()
## 
##  Fisher's Exact Test for Count Data
## 
## data:  .
## p-value = 1
## alternative hypothesis: true odds ratio is not equal to 1
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.2574672 3.3593231
## sample estimates:
## odds ratio 
##  0.9363384
  # Vaginal product use
  cluster_vs_df %>%
    select(cluster, vaginal_products_any) %>%
    table() %>%
    fisher.test()
## 
##  Fisher's Exact Test for Count Data
## 
## data:  .
## p-value = 0.003731
## alternative hypothesis: true odds ratio is not equal to 1
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##   1.600724 34.380074
## sample estimates:
## odds ratio 
##    6.62155
  # Menopause status
  cluster_vs_df %>%
    select(cluster, menopause_status) %>%
    table() %>%
    fisher.test()
## 
##  Fisher's Exact Test for Count Data
## 
## data:  .
## p-value = 1
## alternative hypothesis: true odds ratio is not equal to 1
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.1673623 3.5361298
## sample estimates:
## odds ratio 
##  0.7973135
  # Compare Lactobacillus dominance -----
  vs_psmelt_rel_top %>%
    left_join(
      bind_cols(
        order = ps_vs_hc$order,
        sequence_id = ps_vs_hc$labels,
        cluster = cutree(ps_vs_dend, k = 2)),
      by = "sequence_id"
    ) %>%
    filter(Genus == "Lactobacillus") %>%
    t.test(Abundance ~ cluster, data = .)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  Abundance by cluster

Create clustering and abundance figures for bladder microbiome

sample_names(ps_ur_rel) <- sample_data(ps_ur_rel)$sequence_id
  
  # Clustering work -----
  # Weighted UniFrac to identify distance between samples based on genus
  set.seed(2000)
  ps_ur_f <- UniFrac(ps_ur_rel, weighted = TRUE)
## Warning in UniFrac(ps_ur_rel, weighted = TRUE): Randomly assigning root as --
## GCAAGCGTTGTCCGGATTTACTGGGTGTAAAGGGCGTGTAGGCGGAGAAGCAAGTCAGAAGTGAAATCCATGGGCTTAACCCATGAACTGCTTTTGAAACTGTTTCCCTTGAGTATCGGAGAGGCAGGCGGAATTCCTAGTGTAGCGGTGAAATGCGTAGATATTAGGAGGAACACCAGTGGCGAAGGCGGCCTGCTGGACGACAACTGACGCTGAGGCGCGAAAGCGTG
## -- in the phylogenetic tree in the data you provided.
  set.seed(2001)
  ps_ur_hc <- hclust(ps_ur_f, method = "ward.D2")

  # Convert hclust into a dendrogram
  ps_ur_hcd <- as.dendrogram(ps_ur_hc)

  # Cluster validation
  clmethods <- c("hierarchical")
  internal_val <- clValid(
    as.matrix(ps_ur_f),
    nClust = 2:6,
    clMethods = clmethods,
    validation = "internal")
  
  summary(internal_val)

## Clustering Methods:

  # Setup to color samples
  uhcd_labs_init <-
    ps_ur_hcd %>%
    labels() %>%
    data.frame(sample_id = ., stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
  uhcd_cohort <-
    ps_ur_rel %>%
    sample_data() %>%
    data.frame() %>%
    rownames_to_column("sample_id") %>%
    select(cohort_sufu, sample_name, subject_id, sample_id,
           menopause_status, vaginal_products_any) %>%


  # Specify for cohort information
  # Cases = orange
  # Controls = blue
  mutate(color = if_else(cohort_sufu == "case", "orange", "blue")) %>%
    mutate(shape = if_else(cohort_sufu == "case", 18, 19)) %>%

    # Specify for menopause status
    # Black is post-menopause, White is pre-menopause
    mutate(menopause_stat_color =
             if_else(menopause_status == "Post-Menopause", "black", "white")) %>%

    # Specify vaginal product use
    # Black is vaginal product use, White none
    mutate(vp_use_color =
             if_else(vaginal_products_any == TRUE, "black", "white"))

 
  uhcd_labs <- left_join(uhcd_labs_init, uhcd_cohort, by = "sample_id")

   # Stacked bar plot of taxa -----
  ur_psmelt_rel_top <-
    ps_ur_rel %>%
    psmelt() %>%
    select(sequence_id, Abundance, subject_id, sample_origin,
           sample_name, Phylum, Genus) %>%
    mutate(sequence_id = fct_relevel(sequence_id, uhcd_labs$sample_id))

  # Use same color scheme and legend as vs samples
  color_mdf <-match_cdf(ur_psmelt_rel_top, vs_cdf, df_is_mdf = FALSE)

  plot_ur <- plot_microshades(color_mdf, vs_cdf, x = "sequence_id") +
    theme(axis.title.x = element_blank(),
          axis.text.x = element_blank(),
          axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
          legend.position = "none")

  # Plot dendrogram -----
  # Create parameters and plot dendrogram
  par(mar = c(3, 2, 1, 1))
  origin_mar <- par(no.readonly = TRUE)
  ps_ur_dend <-
    ps_ur_hcd %>%
    dendextend::set("leaves_col", uhcd_labs$color) %>%
    dendextend::set("leaves_pch", uhcd_labs$shape) %>%
    dendextend::set("leaves_cex", 1) %>%
    dendextend::set("labels", rep("", nrow(uhcd_labs)))
  ps_ur_dend %>% plot()
  colored_bars(colors =
                 uhcd_labs %>%
                 select(menopause_stat_color,
                        vp_use_color) %>%
                 rename(MENOP = menopause_stat_color,
                        VPROD = vp_use_color),
               dend = ps_ur_dend,
               sort_by_labels_order = FALSE)
  dendextend::rect.dendrogram(ps_ur_dend, k = 2, border = 8, lty = 5, lwd = 2, lower_rect = -.2)

  par(origin_mar)

  plot_ur

  # both figures use same legend
  plot_grid(vs_legend)

  # Test cluster significance -----
  cluster_ur_df <-
    uhcd_labs %>%
    left_join(
      bind_cols(
        order = ps_ur_hc$order,
        sample_id = ps_ur_hc$labels,
        cluster = cutree(ps_ur_dend, k = 2)),
      by = "sample_id"
    )

  # Cohort
  cluster_ur_df %>%
    select(cluster, cohort_sufu) %>%
    table() %>%
    fisher.test()
